  "title": "Define Stored Source Fields in Your MongoDB Search Index",
  "description": "The storedSource option in a MongoDB Search index definitions specifies the fields in the source document\nthat MongoDB Search must store. You can configure storedSource to improve query\nperformance in certain use cases,\nas it reduces the need for implicit query time lookup on the backend database.\nYou can store fields of all supported types on MongoDB Search.",
